_HSH			User Simple Shell Manual			_HSH

NAME
	hsh - Simple UNIX shell

SYNOPSIS
	hsh

DESCRIPTION
       
	HSH is a custom UNIX command line interpreter which built by C program.
	It supports built-in commands "env" and "exit", custom commands within
	the $PATH environment variables or existing path, and basic error handling
	and alerting.

Invocation
	Simple shell can be run in both interactive and
	non-interactive modes. 

COMMANDS
	Simple_shell supports below built-in commands:
	
	exit (status)
	- Exit simple shell with speficied status.
	- Success - 2

	env
	- Prints current environment variables.

OPTIONS AND ARGUMENTS
	The hsh command does not take any command line options or arguments.

EXAMPLES
	Interactive mode:
	$ ./hsh
	($) /bin/ls
	hsh main.c shell.c

	($) exit
	$
	
	Non-interactive mode:
	$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
	hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
	
	$ cat test_ls_2 | ./hsh
	hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
	hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2

SEE ALSO
       bash(1), sh(1)

